Good question — and here it matters a lot.


---

✅ Where to run the fix

👉 Run ALL recovery commands on:

🔹 controller-0 (ACTIVE controller)


---

📌 Why controller-0?

From your sm-dump:

controller-services   active   go-active   failed

👉 This shows:

controller-0 is trying to become ACTIVE

Only ACTIVE controller can:

Generate .CREDENTIAL

Provide Keystone password

Fix platform services




---

🚀 Exact commands (run ONLY on controller-0)

Step 1:

sudo sm-restart service-group controller-services


---

Step 2: Monitor status

sm-dump | grep controller-services

👉 Wait until:

controller-services active active


---

Step 3: Check credential file

ls -ltr /opt/platform/.keyring/24.09/

👉 Expect:

.CREDENTIAL


---

Step 4: Load credentials

source /etc/platform/openrc

Check:

echo $OS_PASSWORD


---

Step 5: Test

system host-list
system application-list


---

❌ What NOT to do

🚫 Don’t run on:

controller-1 (standby)

worker nodes

storage nodes


👉 It will NEVER work there


---

🧠 Simple Rule

Node	Use for fix?

controller-0	✅ YES
controller-1	❌ NO



---

If you're not 100% sure which is active, run on both:

sm-dump | grep controller-services

👉 The one showing active / go-active = your target node


